HEADWORD: Dentiloquy
<hw>Den*til"o*quy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dens</ets>, <ets>dentis</ets>, tooth + <ets>loqui</ets> to
speak.]</ety> <def>The habit or practice of speaking through the teeth,
or with them closed.</def>⟦br⟧
